         <abstract>
            <p>Durand and Kerner independently have proposed a quadratically convergent iteration method for finding all zeros of a polynomial simultaneously. Here, a new derivation of their iteration equation is given, and a second, cubically convergent iteration method is proposed. A relatively simple procedure for choosing the initial approximations is described, which is applicable to either method.</p>
          </abstract>
